# 🛍️ E-Commerce Sales Data Analytics Dashboard

## 📊 Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing real-world e-commerce sales data to uncover insights about customer behavior, product performance, and revenue trends.  
The dataset contains order records from multiple months, and the goal was to clean, analyze, and visualize the data using **Python** and **Google Looker Studio**.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Clean and preprocess raw e-commerce sales data.
- Explore trends in **sales, revenue, and brand performance**.
- Build an **interactive dashboard** to visualize key business metrics.
- Derive insights for better understanding of customer and product analytics.

---

## 🧰 Tools & Technologies
| Tool | Purpose |
|------|----------|
| **Python (Colab)** | Data Cleaning & Analysis |
| **Pandas, NumPy** | Data Manipulation |
| **Matplotlib, Seaborn** | Exploratory Data Visualization |
| **Google Looker Studio** | Interactive Dashboard Creation |
| **CSV Files (Oct–Dec 2019)** | Raw Data Source |

---

## 🧹 Data Cleaning Steps
- Merged multiple monthly datasets (Oct–Dec 2019).
- Handled missing and duplicate values.
- Extracted month and year from timestamps.
- Converted data types for numerical and categorical analysis.

---

## 📈 Key Metrics (KPIs)
| KPI | Description |
|-----|--------------|
| 💰 **Total Revenue** | Sum of all sales transactions |
| 🧾 **Total Orders** | Count of purchase events |
| 👥 **Unique Customers** | Number of distinct buyers |
| 🛍️ **Total Products Sold** | Unique product IDs sold |

---

## 📉 Dashboard Insights
- **Top Brands by Revenue** — Identified the leading brands generating the most revenue.  
- **Monthly Revenue Trend** — Clear visualization of revenue fluctuations over time.  
- **Category-wise Sales** — Breakdown of total sales by category.  
- **Customer Activity** — Insights into number of active users and purchase frequency.

